article.description: On Wisconsin.  The Badgers moved past Weber State behind 21 points from Kirk Penney.
article.headline: Wisconsin proves it's not strictly about defense
article.story: OGDEN, Utah (AP) -- Lance Allred scored 27 points and Slobodan Ocokoljic sank the winning free throws as Weber State beat Global Sports 74-73 in exhibition play Thursday night. Allred, who went 6-for-6 from the line, tied the game at 71 and put the Wildcats ahead 72-71 with two free throws with 42 seconds to play. Maurice Baker scored for Global to take the lead 73-72. With four seconds left, Ocokoljic, who was 4-for-4 from the line, was fouled by Shawn Daniels and sank the tying and winning free throws. Nic Sparrow added 14 points for the Wildcats, who trailed 40-24 at the half. Adrian Peterson scored 17 points for Global and Daniels had 16, 12 of them in the first half.
